&quot;Titanic Waifs back in Maman's Arms&quot;
From NYTimes dated May 17, 1912.  Their mother came over from France to be reunited with the boys.

&quot;Four-year-old <b>Michel</b> and two-year-old <b>Edmond</b> <b>Navratil</b>, the two waifs who were saved from the sinking Titanic and brought to this city under the temporary guardianship of Miss Margaret Hayes, of 304 West Eighty-third Street, another survivor, are waifs no longer. They have a mother now, just like other children of less romantic and adventurous infancy.&quot;
